
### Creating the Repository on GitHub
1. Go to GitHub and sign in to your account.
2. Click on the `+` button in the upper-right corner and select `New repository`.
3. Enter `OCR-with-Phi-3-Vision` as the repository name.
4. Add the description: "This repository contains code to perform Optical Character Recognition (OCR) on images using the Phi-3 Vision model from Microsoft. The OCR output is provided in markdown format."
5. Choose the visibility (Public or Private).
6. Click on `Create repository`.

### Adding the README file
1. In the newly created repository, click on `Add file` and select `Create new file`.
2. Name the file `README.md`.
3. Copy the content of the README file provided above into the editor.
4. Commit the new file by clicking on `Commit new file`.

### Uploading the Code
1. Clone the repository to your local machine.
2. Copy your code files into the cloned repository directory.
3. Use the following commands to push your code to GitHub:

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit with OCR code"
git push origin main
